The paper discusses methods for learning embeddings of entities and relations in knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the performance of these embeddings on the task of link prediction, which is a common task in the field of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses methods for negative sampling, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
